net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data

Class SQLTableModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data.AbstractTableModel
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data.SQLTableModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JDBCSQLTableModel

    public abstract class SQLTableModel
extends AbstractTableModel

    This class presents a JDBC ResultSet as a TableModel. It is similar in purpose to ResultSetTableModel but has more functionality such as column ordering, etc. It takes an SQL query string, column names and a database source to more efficiently handle the data. The database source is not defined in this class, a subclass must handle it. This allows different methods to access the JDBC API. The ResultSet itself must be JDBC 2.0 compliant.

    The query passed in must not have any ORDER BY or LIMIT clauses. It must be able to have an "ORDER BY field1, field2, .. LIMIT x,y" clause appended to it and be correct.

    This model supports editing of cell values by storing the values in memory. No direct updating of the database is supported. Updating of the values in the database must be done by outside code. See setColumnEditable(int, boolean), getEditedValueAt(int, int) and getEditedRows().

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • isRowValid

        public boolean isRowValid(int row)
        Description copied from class: AbstractTableModel
        This implementation of isRowValid() returns true if the rowIndex is in the interval [0,getRowCount()). Returns true if the row is valid in this model. In general a row should be valid if it is less than the value of getRowCount(). Determining getRowCount() may not be efficient for all models so this method is provided to determine if a given row is valid. It is assumed that if a row is invalid, all the rows with an index greater than the row checked are also invalid.
        Specified by:
        isRowValid in interface TableModel
        Overrides:
        isRowValid in class AbstractTableModel
        Parameters:
        row - The row index.
        Returns:
        true if the row is valid.
